{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> βασκ-αίνω</b>, <br /> <i>future</i> <b>-ᾰνῶ</b>[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX.Deu.28.56 \">LXX</a>]: <i>aorist</i> ἐβάσκηνα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd-3rd c.AD:\">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>] Philostratus Sophista (see. below), <b>-ᾱνα</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Problemata” 926b24:\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>] —<i>passive</i>, <i>aorist</i> ἐβασκάνθην (see. below):—<b>bewitch</b> by the evil eye, etc., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus [same place], LXX.Deu.28.56: _metaphorically_, NT.Gal.3.1; ἐβάσκηνε πάντα.. τύχη 2nd c.AD: Herodianus Grammaticus 2.4.5 \">NT+4th c.BC+</a>]:—<i>passive</i>, ὡς μὴ βασκανθῶσι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Fragmenta” 347; ὡς μὴ βασκανθῶ τρὶς ἔπτυσα 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 6.39. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> with <i>accusative</i>, <b>malign, disparage,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pherecrates Comicus 174, 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 8.19; ἄν τι δύσκολον συμβαίνῃ τοῦτο βασκαίνει [prev. author] 18.189; εἰσίν τινες.. οὓ τὸ βασκαίνειν τπέφει 4th c.BC: Dionysius Comicus 11 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]:—<i>passive</i>, ὑπὸ τῶν ἀντιτέχνων βασκανθῆναι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC-1st c.AD: Strabo Geographus 14.2.7. \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> with <i>dative</i>, <b>envy, grudge,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 20.24, etc.\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; τινί τινος <b>grudge</b> one a thing, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Dio Chrysostomus Sophista 78.37, 2nd-3rd c.AD: Philostratus Sophista “Vita Apollonii” 6.12; τινὶ ἐπί τινι 1st-2nd c.AD: Dio Chrysostomus Sophista 78.25: _absolutely_, 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Nav.” 17: τινός \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]<b>keep to oneself,</b> [<a href=\"javascrip